  "instructions": [
    "Heat oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add onion and garlic, sauté for about 2 minutes until soft.",
    "Stir in tomato paste, soy sauce, lime juice, water or vegetable broth, red pepper flakes, ginger root, and sesame seeds. Bring to a simmer, then reduce heat to low.",
    "Cook fettuccine according to package instructions. Drain pasta and add it back into the skillet with the sauce. Cook for an additional 2-3 minutes until pasta is heated through and sauce coats the noodles evenly.",
    "Serve hot."
